        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:50PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 249 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Bon Air to near
Mitchell Lake. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sylacauga, Childersburg, Goodwater, Rockford, Kellyton, Weogufka,
Stewartville, Oak Grove, Bon Air, Hanover, Lyle, Dollar, Bradford,
Cottage Grove, Strickland Crossroads, Bentleyville, Moriah, Hatchet,
Nixburg, and Mitchell Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
